---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Workflows', url: '/workflows' },
  { name: 'Foaling Management', url: '/workflows/foaling-management' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'When are the pregnancy milestones generated?',
    answer: 'Milestones are auto-generated when you confirm a pregnancy or when ovulation is recorded in a breeding plan. The system calculates dates based on confirmed ovulation or breeding date.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I customize the milestone schedule?',
    answer: 'Yes. While default milestones follow standard equine pregnancy checkpoints (15-day, 45-day, 90-day, 300-day), you can add custom milestones or adjust dates based on your veterinarian\'s recommendations.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does foaling countdown work?',
    answer: 'The foaling countdown shows days remaining until expected foaling for each pregnant mare. Expected dates are calculated from confirmed ovulation (adding ~340 days) or from breeding date. Countdowns appear on dashboards and the foaling calendar.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I track multiple pregnant mares at once?',
    answer: 'Yes. The foaling calendar shows all pregnant mares with their expected and actual foaling dates. Visual color-coding helps you see who is due soon, who is overdue, and upcoming milestone dates.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What pre-foaling signs can I track?',
    answer: 'The pre-foaling checklist includes udder development, waxing (milk droplets), vulvar relaxation, behavior changes, and any custom signs you want to monitor. Each sign can be dated as it appears.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I record foaling outcomes?',
    answer: 'When a mare foals, you record the actual date/time, foal details (sex, color, markings), delivery notes (normal vs. assisted), complications, vet involvement, placenta passage timing, and mare post-foaling condition.'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Foaling Management Workflow | BreederHQ"
  description="Manage horse pregnancy from confirmation to birth. Auto-generated milestones, foaling calendar, pre-foaling checklists, and outcome recording for equine breeders."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:shadow-lg focus:rounded">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <main id="main-content">
  <nav class="breadcrumb py-4 px-4 bg-gray-50" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-sm">
      <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Home</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li><a href="/workflows" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Workflows</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li aria-current="page" class="text-gray-600">Foaling Management</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Foaling Management for Equine Breeders</h1>

      <aside class="tldr-box bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 my-8 rounded" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">TL;DR</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Eleven months is a long time to track manually. BreederHQ auto-generates pregnancy milestones (15-day check, 45-day heartbeat, 90-day development, 300-day monitoring), provides a visual foaling calendar across your program, includes pre-foaling sign checklists, and records complete foaling outcomes. Never miss a critical checkpoint again.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Horse pregnancy is an 11-month journey with critical checkpoints along the way. Missing a 15-day twin check or a 45-day heartbeat confirmation can have serious consequences. Scrambling to remember when each mare is due leads to preventable mistakes.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        BreederHQ tracks it all so you can focus on the care, not the calendar math.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Challenge -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Why foaling management matters</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The stakes in equine pregnancy are high:
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span><strong>Twin pregnancies</strong> — Must be detected early (by day 15-16) for reduction. Missed twins often result in late-term loss.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span><strong>Early pregnancy loss</strong> — Common before day 45. Heartbeat confirmation is critical for knowing you have a viable pregnancy.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span><strong>Long gestation</strong> — 340+ days means dates calculated months ago need to be tracked reliably.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span><strong>Pre-foaling signs</strong> — Udder development, waxing, and behavior changes signal imminent foaling but vary by mare.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span><strong>Dystocia risk</strong> — Being present at foaling can mean the difference between a live foal and a tragedy.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-6 font-semibold">
        When you're managing multiple pregnant mares, a wall calendar and memory aren't enough.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Milestone Tracking -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Auto-Generated Pregnancy Milestones</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        When you record a confirmed breeding or ovulation date, BreederHQ automatically generates a milestone schedule for each pregnancy.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Standard Equine Pregnancy Milestones</h3>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-start border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 mr-4">
              <div class="bg-blue-500 text-white font-bold rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center">15</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold text-lg">Day 15 — First Pregnancy Check</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Ultrasound to confirm pregnancy and detect twins. Twin reduction, if needed, is typically done at this stage.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 mr-4">
              <div class="bg-green-500 text-white font-bold rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center">45</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold text-lg">Day 45 — Heartbeat Confirmation</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Ultrasound confirms fetal heartbeat and viability. Many consider pregnancy "safe" after this point.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start border-l-4 border-yellow-500 pl-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 mr-4">
              <div class="bg-yellow-500 text-white font-bold rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center">90</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold text-lg">Day 90 — Development Check</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Confirms normal fetal development. Some breeders confirm sex via ultrasound around this time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 mr-4">
              <div class="bg-orange-500 text-white font-bold rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center">300</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold text-lg">Day 300 — Monitoring Period Begins</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Increased observation starts. Prepare foaling area, begin pre-foaling sign monitoring.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 mr-4">
              <div class="bg-red-500 text-white font-bold rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center">⚡</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold text-lg">Pre-Foaling Signs Watch</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Checklist for udder development, waxing, vulvar relaxation, and behavior changes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Each milestone shows as upcoming, due, or completed. You'll never wonder "when was her 45-day check supposed to be?" again.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Foaling Calendar -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Foaling Calendar</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        See your entire breeding program's foaling schedule at a glance.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Expected Dates</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Calculated from confirmed ovulation or breeding date. Updated automatically when you record earlier/later ovulation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Visual Timeline</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Color-coded by status: early pregnancy, mid-pregnancy, monitoring period, due soon, overdue.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Countdown Display</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Days until expected foaling for each mare. Sort by soonest-due to see who needs attention first.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Milestone Overlay</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            See upcoming milestones across all mares. Schedule vet visits efficiently when multiple mares need checks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Whether you have 3 pregnant mares or 30, the foaling calendar keeps you organized without spreadsheet gymnastics.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pre-Foaling Signs -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Pre-Foaling Sign Tracking</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Every mare is different. Some wax for days, others foal hours after first signs. Tracking pre-foaling signs helps you learn each mare's pattern and predict when foaling is imminent.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Pre-Foaling Checklist</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded mr-4 flex-shrink-0"></div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold">Udder Development</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Progressive filling, typically begins 2-6 weeks before foaling</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded mr-4 flex-shrink-0"></div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold">Waxing (Milk Droplets)</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Waxy secretion on teats, often 24-48 hours before foaling</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded mr-4 flex-shrink-0"></div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold">Vulvar Relaxation</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Elongation and relaxation of vulva in final days</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded mr-4 flex-shrink-0"></div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold">Tail Head Softening</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Muscles around tail head become soft and relaxed</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded mr-4 flex-shrink-0"></div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold">Behavior Changes</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Restlessness, isolation, nesting behavior</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded mr-4 flex-shrink-0"></div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold">Milk Dripping</p>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Active dripping often signals foaling within hours</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Each sign can be dated when first observed. Over time, you'll build a history of each mare's pre-foaling patterns.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Foaling Outcome Recording -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Foaling Outcome Recording</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        When the foal arrives, complete documentation ensures you have records for registration, veterinary follow-up, and future breeding decisions.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Foaling Details</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Actual foaling date and time</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Normal vs. assisted delivery</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Veterinarian involvement</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Placenta passage timing</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Complications (dystocia, red bag, etc.)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Foal Information</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Sex</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Color and markings</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Birth weight (if measured)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>IgG test results</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Time to stand/nurse</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Mare Post-Foaling</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Mare condition</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Colostrum quality</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Foal heat date tracking</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Rebreeding notes</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Documentation</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Photos at birth</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Veterinary notes attachment</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Free-form notes</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Registration application prep</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Never Miss a Milestone</h2>

      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Auto-generated pregnancy milestones. Visual foaling calendar. Pre-foaling sign tracking. Complete outcome documentation. Everything you need to manage equine pregnancies professionally.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a href="/coming-soon" class="inline-block bg-white text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition text-center" style="min-height: 44px;">
          Get Early Access
        </a>
        <a href="/horses" class="inline-block bg-transparent border-2 border-white text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] transition text-center" style="min-height: 44px;">
          See all horse features →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 faq-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      {faqs.map(faq => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>{faq.question}</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>{faq.answer}</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Related workflows</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-lg">
        <div>
          <a href="/workflows/mare-reproductive-tracking" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">
            → Mare Reproductive Tracking
          </a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <a href="/workflows/stallion-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">
            → Stallion Services Management
          </a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <a href="/workflows/breeding-intelligence" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">
            → Breeding Intelligence Tools
          </a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <a href="/horses" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">
            → Horse Breeding Software Overview
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Sticky Mobile CTA -->
  <div class="fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 p-4 bg-white border-t-2 border-gray-200 shadow-lg md:hidden z-50">
    <a href="/coming-soon" class="block w-full text-center bg-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] text-white px-6 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-[hsl(24,95%,48%)] transition" style="min-height: 44px;">
      Get Early Access
    </a>
  </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    .sr-only {
      position: absolute;
      width: 1px;
      height: 1px;
      padding: 0;
      margin: -1px;
      overflow: hidden;
      clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
      white-space: nowrap;
      border-width: 0;
    }

    .faq-item {
      border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      padding: 1.5rem 0;
    }

    .faq-question {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      list-style: none;
    }

    .faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
      display: none;
    }

    .faq-icon {
      transition: transform 200ms ease;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      margin-left: 1rem;
    }

    details[open] .faq-icon {
      transform: rotate(180deg);
    }

    .faq-answer {
      padding-top: 1rem;
      color: #4b5563;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .faq-answer p {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
